# --- Evidence corpus policy (FS.GG.Governance) -------------------------------
# This repo commits governance evidence AS THE AUDIT RECORD OF RECORD by design
# — that is the repo's purpose. The durable-vs-transient boundary follows the
# SDD transient-artifact taxonomy (ADR-0018; canonical doc: FS-GG/FS.GG.SDD
# docs/reference/artifact-taxonomy.md), tracked here as #85 / FS.GG.SDD#110:
#
#   DURABLE — intentionally committed, do NOT gitignore:
#     * surface-drift baselines (surface/**, *.txt) — these ARE the api-compat
#       contract and the surface-drift gate's source of truth;
#     * golden fixtures + snapshots (tests/**/goldens, **/snapshots) — pinned
#       expected output the tests compare against;
#     * cli-publish-smoke handoff fixtures (tests/**/fixtures/**/readiness/
#       wi-*/governance-handoff.json) — pinned test INPUTS, not regenerable run
#       output; kept committed. The root-anchored readiness/*/ role rule below
#       does not match these nested fixture paths;
#     * .fsgg/*.yml sample + fixture config (governance/policy/capabilities/
#       tooling/release) — authored inputs, not run output;
#     * SDD artifacts (specs/*/spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md, contracts, research).
#
#   TRANSIENT — machine-regenerated per run, never committed (ignored below):
#     * specs/<feature>/readiness/ — per-run readiness evidence (0 committed
#       here; no per-feature re-inclusion whack-a-mole, unlike Rendering);
#     * .fsgg/*.json — CLI-emitted run outputs (gates.json, evidence.json,
#       evidence-reuse.json); authored .fsgg inputs stay committed (normally
#       .yml; the controlled-import reference manifest is the explicit JSON exception);
#     * the SDD shared fragment's regenerable roles (see below).
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Per-feature readiness evidence is transient test output (written into
# specs/<feature>/readiness/); regenerated on every run, never committed.
specs/*/readiness/

# CLI-emitted evidence run outputs (never committed; authored .fsgg inputs are).
# **/ so it matches whether the tool runs at the repo root or inside a
# sample/fixture .fsgg/ dir.
**/.fsgg/*.json
!samples/sdd-reference-gate-set/.fsgg/controlled-imports.json

# --- SDD shared transient-artifact fragment (ADR-0018) — adopted -------------
# Convergence per FS.GG.SDD#110: the SDD lifecycle owns the durable-vs-
# regenerable convention and publishes a shared fragment
# (FS.GG.SDD docs/reference/artifact-taxonomy.md); existing repos adopt it by
# copying its regenerable roles in. The generic build/tooling roles the
# fragment lists (bin/ obj/ artifacts/ TestResults/) are already ignored at the
# top of this file — added here are the roles not covered above. readiness/*/
# is ROOT-ANCHORED: it ignores a root-level readiness/<id>/ (the SDD work-model
# layout) and does NOT match this repo's specs/<feature>/readiness/ (ignored
# above) or the durable tests/**/fixtures/**/readiness/ handoff fixtures.
readiness/*/
nuget-cache/
.tmp/
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

